            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Are you talking about the request logs? Those are displayed [by the dev server](https://github.com/pallets/werkzeug/blob/master/werkzeug/_internal.py#L76). They have nothing to do with `app.logger`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nGeneral advice: Don't use `app.logger` for more complex apps. Instead, just use Python's logging module directly.\r\n\r\nAlso, keep in mind that `app.run()` is not suitable for production - so you should never have the `dev == 0` case ;)"
